videoSnippet.title: These Guys are Awesome || Dubov vs Nepo || Russian Chess Championship (2020)
videoSnippet.description:
Follow me on Instagram for extra content https://www.instagram.com/agadmator/

Daniil Dubov vs Ian Nepomniachtchi
Russian Championship Superfinal, ROUND 9
Gruenfeld, exchange variation (D85)

1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Bb5+ c6 8. Ba4 b5 9. Bb3 a5 10. Nf3 O-O 11. O-O a4 12. Bc2 c5 13. Rb1 Nc6 14. d5 Ne5 15. Nxe5 Bxe5 16. Bh6 Ba6 17. Bxf8 Kxf8 18. f4 Bxc3 19.  Rf3  Qa5 20.  E5  Kg8 21.  Kh1  Rd8 22.  E6  Fxe6 23.  Bxg6  Hxg6 24.  Qc2  Bg7 25.  Rg3  G5 26.  Qg6  Qd2 27.  Rxg5  Qc3 28.  Qxe6 +  Kf8 29.  Re1  Qxe1 + 30.  Qxe1  Bf6 31 .  Qh4  Rd6 32.  Qh7  Ke8 33.  Qg8 +  Kd7 34.  Qa8  Bxg5 35.  Fxg5  C4 36.  H4  B4 37.  Qa7 +  Ke8 38.  Qb8 +  Kf7 39.  Qxb4  Rxd5 40.  Qxa4

The 70th Russian Women's Championship is a 12-player round-robin tournament taking place from 5-16 December 2020 in the Central Chess Club in Moscow, Russia.

Players receive 90 minutes for 40 moves, followed by 30 minutes to the end of the game, with a 30-second increment starting from move one. Official website: ruchess.ru
